markdown-notes-panel_1763067426373.content:
# Fancy Markdown Features Demo This is an example Markdown file showcasing various "fancy" features that AI coding agents often use to create visually appealing and interactive documentation. These elements help make docs more engaging, readable, and professional. ## Headers and Emphasis Use headers for structure: # H1: Main Title ## H2: Section ### H3: Subsection #### H4: Sub-subsection Emphasis for key points: - **Bold text** for importance. - *Italic text* for subtle highlights. - ~~Strikethrough~~ for deprecated info. - `Inline code` for quick snippets. - Underlined text (using HTML for extra flair). ## Lists ### Unordered List - Item one - Item two with **bold** - Nested item - Item three ### Ordered List 1. First step 2. Second step 1. Substep 3. Third step ### Task List - [x] Completed task - [ ] Pending task - [x] Another done ## Code Blocks Syntax-highlighted code blocks are essential for docs: ```python # Python example def greet(name): return f"Hello, {name}!" print(greet("World")) ``` ```javascript // JavaScript example function greet(name) { return `Hello, ${name}!`; } console.log(greet("World")); ``` Inline diff for changes: ```diff - Old line + New line ``` ## Tables Tables organize data neatly: | Feature | Description | Example Usage | |-------------|--------------------------------|---------------| | Headers | Structure sections | # Title | | Lists | Bullet or numbered points | - Item | | Code Blocks | Display code with highlighting | ```python``` | | Images | Embed visuals | ![Alt](url) | Align columns: left, center, right. | Left-Aligned | Center-Aligned | Right-Aligned | |:-------------|:--------------:|--------------:| | Content | Middle | Right | ## Images and Media Embed images for visuals (replace with actual URLs in real docs): ![A dazzling AI-generated image](https://via.placeholder.com/400x200?text=Dazzling+AI+Image) Or GIFs for animations: ![Animated GIF](https://via.placeholder.com/400x200?text=Animated+GIF) ## Links and Buttons Hyperlinks: [Visit xAI](https://x.ai) Custom buttons (using HTML): ## Blockquotes and Callouts > This is a blockquote for quotes or notes. Custom callouts (using emojis and bold): > **Note:** This is an info box. > ‚ÑπÔ∏è Use for tips. > **Warning:** Be careful! > ‚ö†Ô∏è Potential pitfalls. > **Success:** Great job! > ‚úÖ Achievement unlocked. ## Emojis and Icons Emojis add flair: üöÄ üåü üî• Use them in headers: ### Features ‚ú® | Emoji | Shortcode | Meaning | |-------|--------------------------|--------------------| | üòÄ | :grinning: | happy face | | üòÑ | :smile: | smiling | | üòç | :heart_eyes: | love it | | üòÇ | :joy: | laughing tears | | üòé | :sunglasses: | cool | | ü§î | :thinking: | thinking | | üôè | :pray: | thanks / please | | üëç | :thumbsup: | approval | | üëé | :thumbsdown: | disapproval | | üéâ | :tada: | celebration | | üöÄ | :rocket: | progress / launch | | ‚ö° | :zap: | energy / speed | | üî• | :fire: | awesome | | üí° | :bulb: | idea | | üêõ | :bug: | bug report | | ‚úÖ | :white_check_mark: | completed | | ‚ùå | :x: | error / failure | | üìù | :memo: | writing / notes | | üì¶ | :package: | release / delivery | | üîó | :link: | link | | ‚è≥ | :hourglass_flowing_sand: | waiting | Also see: * https://www.webfx.com/tools/emoji-cheat-sheet/ * https://emojipedia.org/ ‚ù§Ô∏è üéÉ ‚úÖ ‚ú® ‚≠ê üî• üëª üò≠ ‚úîÔ∏è ## Footnotes Add references[^1] inline. [^1]: This is a footnote explanation. ## Collapsible Sections

## Math Equations For technical docs, use LaTeX math: Inline: \( E = mc^2 \) Block: \[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-x^2} \, dx = \sqrt{\pi} \] ## Diagrams and Flowcharts Use Mermaid for diagrams (renders in supported viewers like GitHub): ```mermaid graph TD A[Start] --> B{Decision?} B -->|Yes| C[Action 1] B -->|No| D[Action 2] C --> E[End] D --> E ``` Sequence diagram: ```mermaid sequenceDiagram participant User participant AI User->>AI: Query AI->>User: Response ``` ## Horizontal Rules Separate sections with lines: --- ## HTML for Extra Customization
